<h1>Problem 368 - 2003 IMOSL, A5</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>Let \(\mathbb{R}^+\) be the set of all positive real numbers. Find all functions \(f: \mathbb{R}^+ \to \mathbb{R}^+\) that satisfy the following conditions:
<ol><li>\(f(xyz)+f(x)+f(y)+f(z)=f(\sqrt{xy})f(\sqrt{yz})f(\sqrt{zx})\) for all \(x,y,z\in\mathbb{R}^+\)</li> 
<li> \(f(x)\lt f(y)\) for all \(1\le x\lt y\).</li>
</ol></p>
